01:25.719 --> 01:27.346
All right, all right.

01:27.454 --> 01:30.481
Let's go see who we can pick up
in our ROTC uniforms.

01:30.590 --> 01:31.751
<i>Oh, YOU guys go ahead.</i>

01:31.858 --> 01:33.190
I'm meeting Lori Beth over here.

01:33.293 --> 01:34.522
- All right.
- Yeah.

01:34.628 --> 01:36.756
Ship ahoy, girls.

01:36.863 --> 01:39.128
Listen to him.
Listen to him.

01:39.232 --> 01:41.599
He takes one stupid class
a week,

01:41.702 --> 01:44.694
and he thinks he's Popeye.

01:46.173 --> 01:47.663
Hi, Rich.

01:47.774 --> 01:48.867
Oh, hi, Lori Beth.

01:48.976 --> 01:50.807
(Richie chuckles)

01:51.845 --> 01:53.779
My girl. (laughs)

01:54.848 --> 01:58.148
Hey, Rich,
you know Cynthia Holmes?

01:58.251 --> 02:01.016
She invited us
to her cousin's dinner party

02:01.121 --> 02:02.987
at the yacht club
Saturday night.

02:03.090 --> 02:04.580
Hey, no kidding?

02:04.691 --> 02:06.716
You must be getting pretty
buddy-buddy with her, huh?

02:06.827 --> 02:09.693
Not really, but she doesn't have
too many friends at school.

02:13.166 --> 02:15.396
LORI BETH:
Cynthia. Hi. Over here.

02:15.502 --> 02:17.800
Hi, Lori Beth.
Hi, Richie.

02:19.539 --> 02:21.098
Hi, Cynthia.

02:21.208 --> 02:22.971
Hey, Cynthia,
you know, me and Pots

02:23.076 --> 02:25.238
aren't doing anything
Saturday night.

02:25.345 --> 02:28.008
Oh. Have you considered the USO?

02:28.115 --> 02:30.242
Hey, great idea!

02:30.350 --> 02:31.681
The USO?

02:31.785 --> 02:35.278
Yeah, Pots. I hear they got
girls down there that volunteer.

02:35.389 --> 02:37.084
For what?

02:37.190 --> 02:40.422
They help comfort lonely Gls.

02:40.527 --> 02:42.586
I'm lonely, I'm lonely.

02:42.696 --> 02:46.030
RALPH:
Me, too. I need comforting.

02:46.133 --> 02:47.828
(Lori Beth laughs)

02:49.036 --> 02:51.698
Don't you just love
men in uniform?

02:51.805 --> 02:53.569
Only West Pointers.

02:53.674 --> 02:56.142
Oh, listen,
I have the directions

02:56.243 --> 02:57.710
for the yacht club for you.

02:57.811 --> 03:00.303
Let me find them here.

03:06.653 --> 03:07.984
Hey, congrats.

03:08.088 --> 03:09.988
You got your braces
taken off.

03:10.090 --> 03:11.319
Terrific.

03:12.759 --> 03:13.954
<i>II</i>

03:14.061 --> 03:16.052
New blood.

03:18.465 --> 03:21.764
♪ And so, my darling ♪

03:21.868 --> 03:23.268
♪ Please take my hand... ♪

03:23.370 --> 03:25.338
Saturday night, stock car race.

03:25.439 --> 03:27.964
Be there.

03:28.075 --> 03:29.872
That's impossible.

03:36.550 --> 03:38.279
Impossible?

03:38.385 --> 03:41.320
I already have plans.

03:42.355 --> 03:43.584
Conference time.

03:43.690 --> 03:45.522
- Oh, but, Fonz, Lori Beth...
- Now.

03:45.625 --> 03:48.686
♪ My darling,
please take my... ♪

03:48.795 --> 03:51.423
By golly, it is conference time.

03:52.466 --> 03:54.627
Be right with you, AF.

03:56.937 --> 03:58.495
Yeah, Fonz?

03:58.605 --> 04:00.869
Did you hear what
that girl said to me?

04:00.974 --> 04:03.602
I'm gonna call
an ambulance for her.

04:03.710 --> 04:05.144
Well, there's
nothing wrong with her.

04:05.245 --> 04:06.770
Nothing wrong?

04:06.880 --> 04:09.850
Well, Fonz, I just don't think
that she understands, uh...

04:09.950 --> 04:11.884
"Be there."

04:11.985 --> 04:14.977
Let me ask you a question: What
is that Cynthia woman's story?

04:15.088 --> 04:17.990
Well... she comes from
a very wealthy family.

04:18.091 --> 04:20.958
Grew up in an all-girls
school... you know.

04:21.060 --> 04:23.052
Oh, you mean class, society,
stuff like that.

04:23.163 --> 04:24.323
Right.

04:24.431 --> 04:26.729
So if I were you,
I would just, uh,

04:26.833 --> 04:28.802
you know, be a little crafty.

04:28.902 --> 04:31.166
Try a... subtle approach.

04:31.271 --> 04:32.170
Subtle.

04:32.272 --> 04:33.501
I can handle that.

04:33.607 --> 04:35.473
Just takes a little while
longer, that's all.

04:35.575 --> 04:37.908
- Sure, just give it a few days.
- Days?

04:38.011 --> 04:40.309
I'm talking minutes.

04:40.413 --> 04:42.882
Richie's friend is cute.

04:42.983 --> 04:44.314
Fonzie? Yeah.

04:44.417 --> 04:45.783
Cynthia Holmes,

04:45.886 --> 04:48.150
I'd like to introduce you
to Arthur Fonzarelli.

04:48.255 --> 04:50.155
He likes to be called Fonzie.

04:50.257 --> 04:52.418
Fonzie. How quaint.

04:53.460 --> 04:55.394
Quaint back.

04:58.431 --> 04:59.558
Very nice.

04:59.666 --> 05:02.499
And I do mean... nice.

05:02.602 --> 05:03.934
May I?

05:04.037 --> 05:05.368
Certainly.

05:05.472 --> 05:06.769
Minutes.

05:08.942 --> 05:12.742
Now, um, Cynthia, Richie told me
that you spent so much time

05:12.846 --> 05:15.144
in girls' schools,
I figured you missed out

05:15.248 --> 05:18.844
on a lot of good years,
so why don't you and I

05:18.952 --> 05:21.751
just go up
to Inspiration Point together.

05:21.855 --> 05:22.845
Oh, my-

05:22.956 --> 05:24.481
What I mean is that, you know,

05:24.591 --> 05:28.152
Inspiration Point is, like,
one, a very historical site.

05:28.261 --> 05:31.663
So many conquests have...

05:32.699 --> 05:34.463
(laughs):
Conquests?

05:34.568 --> 05:35.865
Oh, history.

05:35.969 --> 05:37.198
Oh, I love history.

05:37.304 --> 05:39.033
It's so exhilarating.

05:39.139 --> 05:40.402
Exhilarating.

05:40.507 --> 05:41.667
Exactly.

05:41.775 --> 05:43.504
See that?
She gets my drift.

05:43.610 --> 05:45.442
Look, why don't
you and Lori Beth

05:45.545 --> 05:49.243
take a walk
while we make history?

05:49.349 --> 05:51.010
Well, sure, Fonz.

05:51.117 --> 05:52.881
Eh, come on, Lori Beth,

05:52.986 --> 05:55.284
let's go shoot some baskets.

05:55.388 --> 05:57.618
He's so romantic.

05:58.992 --> 06:02.451
How'd you like to get historic
right here in the booth?

06:03.496 --> 06:06.489
Oh, Cynthia, do come along.

06:07.500 --> 06:10.129
The cocktail guests are waiting.

06:10.237 --> 06:13.104
I don't mind picking you up
in this... place,

06:13.206 --> 06:15.175
but, uh, must you make me wait?

06:15.275 --> 06:17.175
It's my cousin Millard.

06:17.277 --> 06:19.643
I'm afraid
I really do have to run.

06:19.746 --> 06:22.545
Now, wait a minute,
wait a minute, Mill...

06:22.649 --> 06:24.344
you gotta hold on here,

06:24.451 --> 06:27.079
'cause I'm having a convo
with your cuz.

06:27.187 --> 06:28.814
Convo?

06:28.922 --> 06:32.415
Oh, Millard, I'd like you
to meet Arthur Fonzarelli.

06:32.525 --> 06:34.585
He likes to be called Fonzie.

06:34.694 --> 06:36.026
Hey.

06:36.129 --> 06:37.255
Fonzie...?

06:37.364 --> 06:38.661
Yes, you know,

06:38.765 --> 06:41.757
the way you like
to be called Skippy.

06:48.842 --> 06:51.004
Skippy...!

06:52.579 --> 06:54.638
Yes. How do you do?

06:54.748 --> 06:56.272
- I do great.
-(chuckles)

06:57.317 --> 06:59.251
Perhaps.
But confidentially,

06:59.352 --> 07:01.548
one could never tell
from your appearance.

07:01.655 --> 07:03.748
- Hey, you want to chase this
to the door? -Oh, no, no.

07:03.857 --> 07:05.586
Don't be embarrassed.
It's just that Mother

07:05.692 --> 07:08.127
collects clothing for charity,
and since most of it

07:08.228 --> 07:11.061
is nicer than you have, perhaps
you could find something decent.

07:11.164 --> 07:14.600
Well, no, since Mummy, uh...

07:14.701 --> 07:17.864
dresses you, I think
I'll stick with what I got on.

07:17.971 --> 07:19.302
Are you making fun of Mummy?

07:19.406 --> 07:21.397
Millard...

07:21.508 --> 07:23.499
please don't be mean to Fonzie.

07:23.610 --> 07:25.737
We're going to a historical
landmark together.

07:25.845 --> 07:27.745
Pick me up on Tuesday.

07:27.847 --> 07:29.008
Tuesday!

07:29.115 --> 07:31.015
-(snaps fingers)
- I can't. I'm all booked.

07:31.117 --> 07:33.279
- Well, cancel it.
- No, no, you don't understand.

07:33.386 --> 07:34.615
See, Beatrice, Rachel and Ellen

07:34.721 --> 07:36.849
have been waiting
for six months on a list.

07:36.957 --> 07:38.219
Three girls at once?

07:38.325 --> 07:39.519
Well, that's
just on the weekends.

07:39.626 --> 07:41.958
Tuesdays they work in shifts.

07:42.062 --> 07:43.188
Now, listen, sweet lips,

07:43.296 --> 07:45.697
I got to get back
to the garage, all right?

07:45.799 --> 07:47.960
Oh, wait a minute,
wait a minute, wait a minute.

07:48.068 --> 07:49.797
Listen, why don't you
get my phone number

07:49.903 --> 07:51.063
from the bathroom wall--

07:51.171 --> 07:54.106
maybe there's gonna be
a cancellation, huh?

07:54.207 --> 07:56.335
Whoa!

07:56.443 --> 07:58.434
<i>Whoa!</i>

08:05.552 --> 08:06.849
Garage?!

08:06.953 --> 08:09.013
You were going out
with a lowly mechanic?

08:09.122 --> 08:12.683
Worse-- I've just been
turned down by a lowly mechanic.

08:12.792 --> 08:14.192
Mm. Want to get even?

08:14.294 --> 08:16.194
We'll invite him
to my party at the club.

08:16.296 --> 08:17.559
Oh, Skippy.

08:17.664 --> 08:19.996
No, no, no, amongst
the commodore and his friends,

08:20.100 --> 08:22.728
this Fonzie will look like
a court jester... (chuckles)

08:22.836 --> 08:28.240
Oh, Skippy,
what a wonderful idea.

08:28.341 --> 08:30.901
You know, it really
could be quite amusing.

08:31.011 --> 08:32.477
Oh, too, too amusing.

08:32.578 --> 08:33.773
(chuckles)

08:36.383 --> 08:38.374
(mouthing)

08:40.587 --> 08:43.147
<i>RICHIE:
Well, that's what Alfred said.</i>

08:43.256 --> 08:45.748
Imagine, trying
to humiliate him like that.

08:45.859 --> 08:49.591
Richard, you've got
to tell Arthur not to go.

08:49.696 --> 08:52.597
Well... Al and I
didn't really have the heart.

08:52.699 --> 08:54.030
Well, look, you're an adult--

08:54.134 --> 08:56.227
just come out
and tell him the truth.

08:56.336 --> 08:58.168
I think you're right. That's
what I'm gonna have to do.

08:58.271 --> 09:01.002
Yeah, and when you're in the
hospital, can I have your room?

09:02.976 --> 09:05.877
Hey, listen, I'm very sorry
for the interruption right here,

09:05.979 --> 09:09.608
but I want to show you
a flash of class. Look at that.

09:09.716 --> 09:12.583
That's my first invitation
from Cynthia.

09:12.685 --> 09:14.711
Raised letters,
and it ain't even a wedding.

09:14.821 --> 09:16.186
Can you dig that?

09:16.289 --> 09:17.916
Yes, Richard got one, too.

09:18.024 --> 09:20.049
We-we rubbed it before.

09:20.160 --> 09:22.492
Yeah. But the thing is, dig it,

09:22.595 --> 09:25.690
this is my first RSVP.

09:25.799 --> 09:29.599
Usually I just get,
you know, "Stag" or "Drag."

09:29.702 --> 09:32.467
- Oh, Arthur...
- Yeah?

09:32.572 --> 09:34.131
Richard.

09:34.240 --> 09:36.402
- Howard...
- Marion...

09:36.509 --> 09:39.001
I think maybe
you better leave us men alone

09:39.112 --> 09:40.545
for a few minutes, huh?

09:40.647 --> 09:43.582
Yes. Come on, Joanie,
let's, uh, defrost the roast.

09:43.683 --> 09:47.984
- Oh, I miss all the fireworks.
- You're catching on.

09:48.088 --> 09:50.056
What are we gonna do,
tell dirty jokes?

09:51.091 --> 09:53.525
Fonz, look, about this party...

09:53.626 --> 09:55.526
- Yeah.
- I think it's gonna be boring.

09:55.628 --> 09:58.291
I'd much rather go
to the stock car races with you.

09:58.398 --> 10:00.525
I mean, it's great--
(imitate tires skidding)

10:00.633 --> 10:02.101
Skidding through turns.

10:02.202 --> 10:03.601
(imitates crashing)

10:03.703 --> 10:04.693
Wipeout!

10:04.804 --> 10:06.363
You know, that's my kind of fun.

10:06.473 --> 10:08.600
You don't have
to beat around the bush with me;

10:08.708 --> 10:09.675
I get your drift.

10:09.776 --> 10:11.471
- Oh, you do?
- Sure.

10:11.578 --> 10:13.671
This is gonna be a different
type of party for you.

10:13.780 --> 10:14.610
You're gonna be lonely.

10:14.714 --> 10:16.705
I'll take care of you-- promise.

10:18.718 --> 10:21.051
Dad?
(clears throat softly)

10:22.088 --> 10:24.751
(sighs)
Uh...

10:24.858 --> 10:27.884
Fonzie,
when-when-when I was a kid,

10:27.994 --> 10:30.588
uh, my father used
to tag along with me

10:30.697 --> 10:32.187
at all the school dances.

10:32.298 --> 10:35.996
Now, he was a nice guy,
but he just didn't fit in.

10:36.102 --> 10:38.696
Can you understand
what I'm saying?

10:38.805 --> 10:39.863
Sure.

10:39.973 --> 10:41.270
And I hope that, one day,

10:41.374 --> 10:45.334
you can sit down with your pop
and have a long talk.

10:47.147 --> 10:48.637
Richard...

10:50.517 --> 10:52.246
Fonzie, don't go to the party.

10:52.352 --> 10:53.683
They only invited you there

10:53.786 --> 10:55.118
'cause they want
to make fun of you.

10:57.991 --> 10:59.959
They want to make fun of me?

11:02.161 --> 11:04.528
Who wants to make fun of me?

11:04.631 --> 11:06.258
Cynthia and-and Millard.

11:06.366 --> 11:07.526
No, no, not Cynthia.

11:07.634 --> 11:09.534
Cynthia, she sent me
this invitation,

11:09.636 --> 11:11.103
with raised letters
and everything, man.

11:11.204 --> 11:12.569
She likes me.

11:12.672 --> 11:14.663
I mean, you know, Millard,
he's not one

11:14.774 --> 11:17.107
of my favorite people
in the whole world-- so what?

11:17.210 --> 11:19.269
Hey, I'll tell you something,
I'll tell you something,

11:19.379 --> 11:21.472
I'll just watch my P's and Q's,
that's all.

11:21.581 --> 11:24.209
You know,
like they say in society...

11:24.317 --> 11:26.149
ta-ta.

11:27.186 --> 11:29.178
Heyyy!

11:34.027 --> 11:36.518
Well, you didn't exactly
talk him out of it.

11:36.629 --> 11:37.722
Mm.

11:37.830 --> 11:39.924
It looks like
Arthur's going to dinner.

11:40.033 --> 11:41.762
Not only is he going to dinner,

11:41.868 --> 11:44.530
it looks like he's going
to be the main course.

11:52.512 --> 11:54.639
<i>AL: Better hurry up, Fonz.
It's getting late.</i>

