12:05.725 --> 12:07.716
Oh, Fonz, you look great!

12:07.827 --> 12:11.024
- Perfect fit.
- Bellissimo!

12:11.130 --> 12:13.292
With four arms?

12:17.036 --> 12:18.766
Four arms!

12:18.871 --> 12:20.863
You only gave me
two dollars for it.

12:20.974 --> 12:23.238
I got it off of Ollie
the Human Octopus

12:23.343 --> 12:24.776
at the circus sideshow.

12:24.877 --> 12:27.847
Ollie's a phony?

12:27.947 --> 12:30.314
I shook hands with him.

12:31.351 --> 12:32.614
Now, look...

12:32.719 --> 12:35.449
I'm gonna wear
my leather jacket.

12:35.555 --> 12:37.853
It's proper for any occasion.

12:37.957 --> 12:40.290
Get out of here.

12:40.393 --> 12:42.384
Sorry, Fonz, I tried.

12:43.429 --> 12:45.227
Hey, wait a minute...

12:45.331 --> 12:48.096
maybe I could sell it
to Ralph and Potsie.

12:51.938 --> 12:55.670
(seabirds squawk in distance)

12:55.775 --> 12:57.766
(piano playing lively jazz)

13:05.284 --> 13:07.617
(blows bosun's whistle)

13:08.621 --> 13:10.919
Piping aboard.

13:11.024 --> 13:15.017
Miss Lori Beth Allen
and Richard Cunningham.

13:18.264 --> 13:21.097
- How do you do?
- How do you do? How do you do?

13:23.102 --> 13:26.038
(blows whistle)

13:26.139 --> 13:28.539
Piping aboard.

13:28.641 --> 13:31.042
Mr. and Mrs. Simpson.

13:34.981 --> 13:37.245
I don't see Fonzie;
I wonder if he's coming.

13:37.350 --> 13:38.647
Oh, no, no, he's coming.

13:38.751 --> 13:40.048
I... I saw the Polanski twins

13:40.153 --> 13:42.781
pumping air
into his motorcycle tires.

13:45.858 --> 13:48.225
(Fonzie whistles)

13:48.328 --> 13:49.317
All right.

13:49.429 --> 13:50.487
Now, hear this:

13:50.596 --> 13:53.589
The Fonz is here--
let the frolics begin.

13:55.201 --> 13:58.034
How do? How do? How do?

13:58.137 --> 14:00.106
How do? How do?

14:00.206 --> 14:02.197
How do you do?

14:10.216 --> 14:12.617
Excuse me, Cynthia,
I just want to show Fonzie

14:12.719 --> 14:14.243
the great view of Lake Michigan.

14:14.354 --> 14:15.651
<i>Oh, no, no, no, no.</i>

14:15.755 --> 14:18.087
I wanted to introduce Fonzie
to some of our friends.

14:18.191 --> 14:20.091
This is the Commodore.

14:20.193 --> 14:22.024
Oh, uh, how do you do?

14:22.128 --> 14:23.721
He's a little deaf.

14:23.830 --> 14:25.798
Come, Fonzie, I want you
to meet some more people.

14:25.898 --> 14:28.458
- RICHIE: Uh, no!
- FONZIE: See ya, see ya, see ya.

14:28.568 --> 14:30.832
How do? How do? How do?

14:30.937 --> 14:32.734
Hey. Nice to see ya.

14:32.839 --> 14:34.136
All right, ship ahoy.

14:37.543 --> 14:40.445
So glad you could come.
(chuckles)

14:40.546 --> 14:43.209
A leather blazer-- how gauche.

14:43.316 --> 14:45.512
Good. How gauche it with you?

14:46.919 --> 14:48.819
Hey, eats! All right!

14:48.921 --> 14:51.857
I never heard caviar
referred to as "eats."

14:51.958 --> 14:53.391
Caviar?

14:53.493 --> 14:55.586
Yes, sir, they're
little fish eggs.

14:55.695 --> 14:57.492
It's imported. Eat up.

14:57.597 --> 15:00.088
Imported little fish eggs.

15:00.199 --> 15:02.099
How quaint.

15:02.201 --> 15:04.431
I had 'em for lunch;
thanks very much, anyway.

15:04.537 --> 15:07.165
Juanita,
that will be enough out of you.

15:07.273 --> 15:09.298
Wait a minute,
she's just being friendly.

15:09.409 --> 15:11.138
We don't hire servants
to be friendly.

15:11.244 --> 15:12.541
We hire them to work.

15:12.645 --> 15:15.080
(bosun's whistle blows)

15:15.181 --> 15:17.081
Dinner is served.

15:17.183 --> 15:18.708
Hey, uh, Juanita...

15:18.818 --> 15:21.480
thanks a lot for the tip
on the little fishies, huh?

15:21.587 --> 15:23.078
- Heyyy.
- Come, Millard.

15:23.189 --> 15:25.282
Uh, yes, come along,
Mr. Fonzarelli.

15:25.391 --> 15:28.054
Dinner is ready.
hurry along, now.

15:28.161 --> 15:29.526
Chow, chow.

15:29.629 --> 15:31.222
(chuckles):
"Chow, chow."

15:31.330 --> 15:33.560
Hey, I love Chinese food.

15:42.074 --> 15:44.373
I want to tell you something,
I really like that soup.

15:44.477 --> 15:46.138
- What is it?
- Vichyssoise.

15:46.245 --> 15:49.442
Oh, it tasted
like potatoes to me.

15:49.549 --> 15:52.643
- It is potato.
- I knew the soup.

15:52.752 --> 15:54.686
I knew the soup!

15:54.787 --> 15:56.915
I know my veggies.
(chuckles)

15:59.325 --> 16:02.056
Perhaps Mr. Fonzarelli
would like to choose

16:02.161 --> 16:03.993
the next bottle of wine.

16:04.096 --> 16:06.156
- I'll do it! -I'll do it!
- CYNTHIA: No, no...

16:06.265 --> 16:08.256
let Fonzie do it.

16:13.072 --> 16:14.631
Perhaps a hint.

16:14.740 --> 16:16.470
We're having lobster.

16:16.576 --> 16:18.567
Flown in from Maine, of course.

16:18.678 --> 16:20.475
Of course. I wouldn't
want those little guys

16:20.580 --> 16:22.070
to walk here all by themselves.

16:25.351 --> 16:28.252
We have an excellent
wine cellar here.

16:28.354 --> 16:31.153
Perhaps a Mouton Cadet,
a Pinot Chardonnay

16:31.257 --> 16:33.658
or a, uh,
a Chateauneuf-du-Pape?

16:36.496 --> 16:37.861
What's your choice?

16:37.964 --> 16:39.557
Number 11.

16:40.533 --> 16:43.332
A Pouilly Fuissé, uh, 1949.

16:43.436 --> 16:45.563
An excellent choice, sir.

16:45.671 --> 16:48.038
He got the wine!
Fonz, you got the wine!

16:48.140 --> 16:50.302
I got the wine.

16:53.579 --> 16:55.070
(whispering)

16:55.181 --> 16:56.740
Yes, uh, an excellent choice.

16:56.849 --> 16:58.818
Don't you think so, Sappy?

17:01.387 --> 17:03.287
That's Skippy.

17:03.389 --> 17:05.050
Of course.

17:06.559 --> 17:09.926
Millard, he is making
a sap out of you.

17:10.029 --> 17:12.156
The evening isn't over yet.

17:16.801 --> 17:17.791
Pardon me.

17:17.904 --> 17:18.893
(inhales)

17:19.005 --> 17:21.132
It is customary
at these occasions

17:21.240 --> 17:24.938
to have one of the guests
offer a toast to the ladies.

17:25.044 --> 17:27.273
I think it would be
most appropriate

17:27.380 --> 17:31.976
for Mr. Fonzarelli to do
the honors-- don't you think so?

17:40.660 --> 17:44.494
Uh, a toast
to the ladies at my table.

17:44.597 --> 17:47.191
I think you remind me...

17:47.300 --> 17:49.825
of a bouquet.

17:49.936 --> 17:52.837
Lovely, lovely flowers...

17:56.275 --> 17:58.505
...with great stems!

18:00.246 --> 18:02.578
(guests clinking glasses)

18:08.621 --> 18:11.181
Juanita, I won't have a servant
mingling with the guests!

18:11.290 --> 18:13.315
Hey, hold it, she ain't
mingling, she's laughing.

18:13.426 --> 18:16.020
Juanita, I warned you before--
now, get out, you're fired.

18:16.128 --> 18:18.256
-(Fonzie snaps fingers)
- Hold it! Get back here!

18:18.364 --> 18:21.265
Oh, man, there's
gonna be trouble.

18:21.367 --> 18:23.392
Now, wait a minute,
wait a minute, I'm cool.

18:23.502 --> 18:26.062
I just have a few words here
to say to Skippy.

18:27.106 --> 18:30.007
Now, uh, Skip-face...

18:30.109 --> 18:32.544
ever since I got here
to this little get-together,

18:32.645 --> 18:34.078
you've been pushing me
around, see?

18:34.180 --> 18:35.409
That's okay. I'm cool.

18:35.514 --> 18:36.846
I can take care of myself.

18:36.949 --> 18:40.852
When you start pushing little
ladies around, you gone too far.

18:40.953 --> 18:43.513
- CYNTHIA: He's right.
-(Millard huffs)

18:43.623 --> 18:45.557
After all, who'll serve dinner?

18:45.658 --> 18:47.717
(low, indistinct chatter)

18:49.795 --> 18:51.695
"Who'll serve dinner?"

18:51.797 --> 18:53.561
That's what
you're worried about?

18:53.666 --> 18:55.566
Who will serve dinner?

18:55.668 --> 19:00.196
Boy, did you turn out to be
a disappointment, Cynth.

19:00.306 --> 19:03.037
All right, all right,
who is gonna serve dinner, then?

19:03.142 --> 19:05.941
Oh, let me say...

19:06.045 --> 19:08.207
permit me.

19:11.250 --> 19:12.547
Millard...

19:12.652 --> 19:14.643
some lobster.

19:23.462 --> 19:24.987
Let me tell you something.

19:25.097 --> 19:27.498
Don't you ever
call me for a date.

19:27.600 --> 19:29.762
I only date chicks with class.

19:29.869 --> 19:32.269
Well, I never!

19:32.371 --> 19:34.431
Well, honey,
maybe that's your problem.

19:36.509 --> 19:37.840
Hey!

19:41.847 --> 19:45.306
Somebody help me--
I have a lobster on my lap.

19:45.418 --> 19:48.046
Ooh, that Fonzie
is such a common person.

19:48.154 --> 19:49.985
Positively gross.

19:51.023 --> 19:53.617
Okay, buddy, that's it!

19:53.726 --> 19:56.422
You and Cynthia have been
needling Fonzie all night.

19:56.529 --> 19:58.224
You got what you deserved.

19:58.330 --> 19:59.798
You're-you're crude

19:59.899 --> 20:02.163
and-and you're boring and...

20:02.268 --> 20:03.531
- Rotten!
- Right!

20:03.636 --> 20:05.934
- You're not a nice person.
- What makes you think

20:06.038 --> 20:07.802
you're better than my friend
Arthur Fonzarelli?

20:07.907 --> 20:10.137
Maybe he doesn't have
white pants and a blue blazer,

20:10.242 --> 20:11.733
but I'll tell you
one thing, buddy,

20:11.844 --> 20:13.243
he's got something
you'll never have--

20:13.345 --> 20:14.438
he's got class!

20:14.547 --> 20:16.481
Yeah, that's right,
I said class.

20:16.582 --> 20:19.142
- Let's get out of here.
- MILLARD: Yes, steward,

20:19.251 --> 20:21.151
show this common trash
to the door.

20:21.253 --> 20:24.314
Common trash?

20:24.423 --> 20:26.118
Oh, excuse me.

20:26.225 --> 20:30.685
I'm sorry, but you've just seen
common trash pushed too far.

20:34.433 --> 20:35.867
You're forgetting one thing

20:35.968 --> 20:38.733
that goes very well
with lobster--

20:38.838 --> 20:40.772
melted butter.

20:40.873 --> 20:42.864
(Cynthia gasping)

20:55.721 --> 20:58.987
♪ ...my love ♪

20:59.091 --> 21:01.082
♪ You're the only one ♪

21:01.193 --> 21:04.425
IIsee ♪

21:04.530 --> 21:07.363
♪ God only knows ♪

21:07.466 --> 21:09.526
♪ You're the one I dream of... ♪

21:09.635 --> 21:10.864
Hi, Fonz.

21:10.970 --> 21:12.199
<i>II</i>

21:12.304 --> 21:13.271
(music stops)

21:13.372 --> 21:14.931
Hey, Rich.
Listen, uh, girls,

21:15.040 --> 21:17.874
I would like to talk to Rich
on the QT, all right?

21:17.977 --> 21:20.241
(laughs)
Let's powder our noses.

21:20.346 --> 21:22.678
They want to be alone.

21:25.284 --> 21:27.446
You know,
about that Cynthia girl,

21:27.553 --> 21:29.453
you were absolutely right.

21:29.555 --> 21:32.251
I let a beautiful girl
fog my brain.

21:32.358 --> 21:34.827
Well, it happens
to the best of us.

21:34.927 --> 21:36.691
Yeah, but what
I really want to say is

21:36.796 --> 21:39.629
that I am very, uh, s... s...

21:42.001 --> 21:44.936
Richie, I am sincerely...

21:45.037 --> 21:47.131
S... S... S...

21:47.239 --> 21:50.038
Fonz, you don't have
to say you're sorry.

21:50.142 --> 21:53.135
Good. I won't.

21:53.245 --> 21:55.179
But, uh...
I didn't do too good there,

21:55.281 --> 21:58.250
and they probably tossed you out
on my account; I know that.

21:58.350 --> 21:59.317
You kidding?

21:59.418 --> 22:00.818
Think I was gonna
stick around there

22:00.920 --> 22:02.683
after what they did to you?

22:02.788 --> 22:05.382
Are you telling me
that you left on your own?

22:05.491 --> 22:09.928
Yeah. Uh, after I corrected
the one small mistake you made.

22:10.029 --> 22:12.623
You never serve lobster
in a man's lap...

22:12.731 --> 22:14.427
without melted butter.

22:14.533 --> 22:17.002
You did that?

22:17.102 --> 22:18.536
- Yeah.
- You did that?

22:18.637 --> 22:20.105
(laughs):
The whole pitcher.

22:20.206 --> 22:21.571
Well, you know,
it goes together.

22:21.674 --> 22:23.801
Yeah. I'll tell you something,
like you and me,

22:23.909 --> 22:26.310
we go together like lobster
and melted butter, right?

22:26.412 --> 22:29.074
Right, right. Like, uh,
peanut butter and jelly.

22:29.181 --> 22:30.672
(laughs):
Yeah, right.

22:30.783 --> 22:32.580
I hate peanut butter and jelly.

22:35.521 --> 22:37.455
But I know exactly
what you mean.

22:37.556 --> 22:39.047
- Uh-huh.
- Yeah.

22:39.158 --> 22:41.752
So I just want to say thanks,
and I'm thinking

22:41.861 --> 22:44.125
maybe we could have
our own little party, huh?

22:44.230 --> 22:45.458
That's a great idea.

22:45.564 --> 22:47.089
How about
a little, uh, music, maestro?

22:47.199 --> 22:49.190
-(snaps fingers)
- Right.

22:52.504 --> 22:56.100
(song resumes)

22:56.208 --> 22:58.905
♪ Nothing matters ♪

22:59.011 --> 23:00.206
♪ To me... ♪

23:00.312 --> 23:01.211
Oh, where's Juanita?

23:01.313 --> 23:02.144
We're gonna have a party.

23:02.248 --> 23:03.510
She'll be out in a minute.

23:03.616 --> 23:05.174
She's reading the walls.

23:06.218 --> 23:09.882
Oh, Fonzie,
I read all about you.

23:11.991 --> 23:16.018
Never believe what you read--
I'm much better in person.

23:17.062 --> 23:19.088
Lori Beth?

23:19.198 --> 23:21.496
Is there anything
in there about me?

23:21.600 --> 23:23.500
Yeah. It says...

23:26.138 --> 23:27.970
(chuckles):
It does?

23:28.073 --> 23:30.508
I wrote it.

23:33.112 --> 23:35.103
<i>II</i>

23:52.831 --> 23:54.595
(music playing on radio)

23:54.700 --> 23:56.134
♪ There ♪

23:56.235 --> 23:57.862
♪ In the gleam of your ♪

23:57.970 --> 23:59.699
♪ Deep hazel eyes... ♪

23:59.805 --> 24:01.466
This is kind of romantic,

24:01.573 --> 24:03.872
being alone...

24:03.976 --> 24:05.774
soft lights and music.

24:05.878 --> 24:07.402
Mm.

24:07.513 --> 24:10.004
You're what makes it
romantic, sweetheart.

24:10.115 --> 24:12.641
Oh, Howard,
you and your sweet talk.

24:12.751 --> 24:14.378
I love it.

24:17.356 --> 24:18.619
Huh?

24:18.724 --> 24:20.249
RICHIE:
Oh... (chuckles)

24:21.293 --> 24:22.784
Mom and Dad, uh...

24:22.895 --> 24:25.387
-you're still up, huh?
- HOWARD: That's right.

24:25.497 --> 24:27.727
- MARION: Hi, Lori Beth. Oh...!
- Lori Beth.

24:27.833 --> 24:30.200
How did Arthur do at the party?

24:30.302 --> 24:32.327
- Oh, he did fine.
- Oh, yeah, they're...

24:32.438 --> 24:34.201
they're never gonna forget him.

24:34.306 --> 24:35.865
Oh, good.

24:35.975 --> 24:38.136
I love it when things work out.

24:45.117 --> 24:48.109
- Dad...
- We were here first, Richard.

